{"key":"processedPost-14555245","value":{"id":14555245,"first":14510792,"last":14578433,"when":1307123424,"utime":"06/03/11 08:50 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>Luger0815 said:</strong><br />after the dunk, i like to let the bulk-surface dry, before i mist again.<br />Stuff the bigger holes with polyfill (very loose), and wait until the surface is dry again before you mist again.<br />It is better to mist heavy, every other day and wait until it is dry again, instead of keeping the surface moist all the time.<br />It is also time to start the next growth, IMO.</blockquote><br />That's a good way to cause trich to bloom.&nbsp; Don't allow the surface to ever dry totally out.&nbsp; If so, the mushroom mycelium dies back and trich is stimulated next time you mist.<br />It's important to allow some drying, but not 48 hours worth.&nbsp; It's far better to mist daily or even two or three times daily, as this is good insurance against molds.<br />RR"}}